  "text": "Pervasiveness and lower cost of mobile technologies facilitate faster, better and affordable healthcare services. Regular pain assessment is necessary for the presence of pain and for improvement, deterioration, or complications attributable to pain treatment [CITATION_1] . With the help of pervasive computing systems, healthcare professionals (providers and researchers) may deliver more appropriate treatments to patients by leveraging self-reported and automated pain level detection. Accurate assessment of pain is critical for the identification of appropriate interventions and for evaluating the effectiveness of such interventions in the clinical setting [CITATION_2] .",
